  <p>
    Modals are being used to draw attention to vital pieces of information.
  </p>

  <h5>Use cases</h5>

  <ul>
    <li>
      Blocking the application flow until information required to continue is
      entered, as for example a password in a login process.
    </li>
    <li>
      Collecting application configuration options in a centralized dialog.
      In such cases, typically the changes are applied upon closing the dialog,
      and access to the application is disabled while the edits are being made.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <blockquote>
    "When something does need fixing, it's better to make sure that the user knows about it" - Jakob Nielsen
  </blockquote>

